author: @sandeeppanchal8615
text: Another scenario- before splitting the data, suppose we 'fit' vectorizer like BoW or TFIDF, etc, on the whole data set and after splitting, we will 'transform' both train and test set. Since the entire data has already been fitted to vectorizer, after split, transforming test set means data leakage. Only after splitting, 'fit_transform' should be done on train set and 'trasform' on test set (also CV set if created).
